WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:11.000
Well, I need your special talent for handling special matters.

00:11.000 --> 00:14.000
Like what special matters?

00:14.000 --> 00:17.000
Well, I have scheduling problems.

00:17.000 --> 00:18.000
Yes.

00:18.000 --> 00:22.000
I have three tons select to be set for Friday with Dr. Earl.

00:22.000 --> 00:23.000
Yes.

00:23.000 --> 00:27.000
I need to fit a fourth operation into his schedule.

00:27.000 --> 00:30.000
And I know you can do it.

00:30.000 --> 00:32.000
Who's the patient?

00:32.000 --> 00:35.000
Carl Herrera, the boy has infected tonsils,

00:35.000 --> 00:37.000
and we should remove them as soon as possible.

00:37.000 --> 00:39.000
And I'll try to arrange this schedule, Dr. Stewart,

00:39.000 --> 00:42.000
but it's not going to be easy.

00:42.000 --> 00:43.000
Thank you.

00:43.000 --> 00:45.000
I know you'll be able to take care of it.

00:45.000 --> 00:46.000
Oh.

00:46.000 --> 00:51.000
Well, Mrs. Herrera, Carl will be perfectly fine

00:51.000 --> 00:53.000
after we remove his tonsils.

00:53.000 --> 00:56.000
Thank you for your real short, and, Dr. Stewart,

00:56.000 --> 00:59.000
he's had so many coals and sore throats recently.

00:59.000 --> 01:01.000
Well, it's a very easy operation, Carl.

01:01.000 --> 01:03.000
You won't feel a thing.

01:03.000 --> 01:05.000
But when do they do it?

01:05.000 --> 01:07.000
This Friday.

01:07.000 --> 01:10.000
But Saturday's my birthday.

01:10.000 --> 01:15.000
Well, we could rescheduled the operation, Mrs. Herrera,

01:15.000 --> 01:17.000
but I don't want to put it off too long.

01:17.000 --> 01:20.000
No, I think it's important to do it now.

01:20.000 --> 01:22.000
We can have a birthday party for you, Carl,

01:22.000 --> 01:24.000
when you come out of the hospital.

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
But you won't be on my birthday.

01:26.000 --> 01:28.000
But your house isn't more important, Carl.

01:28.000 --> 01:31.000
Believe me, I don't want my tonsils out.

01:35.000 --> 01:37.000
Aner spaker, would you come in, please?

01:42.000 --> 01:44.000
Hello, Mrs. Herrera.

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
Hi, Carl.

01:46.000 --> 01:47.000
How are you doing?

01:47.000 --> 01:51.000
I don't want my tonsils out.

01:51.000 --> 01:52.000
Come with me, Carl.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.000
You and I will talk this over.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.000
She has a special way with kids.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
She sure does.

02:06.000 --> 02:08.000
Carl, does she throw it heard?

02:08.000 --> 02:09.000
Yes.

02:09.000 --> 02:10.000
Okay.

02:10.000 --> 02:12.000
Do you want to get better?

02:12.000 --> 02:13.000
Yes.

02:13.000 --> 02:14.000
Okay.

02:14.000 --> 02:15.000
We want you to get better, too.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.000
Have your tonsils out tomorrow,

02:17.000 --> 02:19.000
and you won't get so many coals anymore.

02:19.000 --> 02:22.000
But if I ask my tonsils out tomorrow,

02:22.000 --> 02:25.000
I'll miss my birthday party on Saturday.

02:25.000 --> 02:26.000
I know.

02:26.000 --> 02:29.000
That's a problem, isn't it?

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
Let me try to work something out.

02:32.000 --> 02:33.000
What?

02:33.000 --> 02:35.000
I have to think about it.

02:35.000 --> 02:37.000
You're fooling me.

02:37.000 --> 02:39.000
Oh, I'm not, Carl.

02:39.000 --> 02:41.000
Give me a chance to think about it,

02:41.000 --> 02:43.000
and I'll come up with something.

02:43.000 --> 02:44.000
So, prize?

02:44.000 --> 02:45.000
Maybe.

02:45.000 --> 02:47.000
But you just put on your pajamas and robe,

02:47.000 --> 02:50.000
and now think of a surprise.

02:50.000 --> 02:51.000
Will it hurt?

02:51.000 --> 02:52.000
No.

02:52.000 --> 02:53.000
There are other boys and girls here,

02:53.000 --> 02:55.000
and they're having their tonsils out.

02:55.000 --> 02:56.000
You'll meet them.

02:56.000 --> 02:58.000
I don't want to.

02:58.000 --> 03:00.000
Change your clothes, Carl.

03:00.000 --> 03:03.000
Everything will be justified.

